Pillar 3 — SkillSetu: The Rural Agricultural Gig-Work Board
What it is
SkillSetu is a hyper-localised gig-work board designed specifically for the agricultural sector's skilled labour needs. It connects rural youth who possess technical skills (tractor repair, irrigation system maintenance, cold storage operation, combine harvester operation, crop spraying) with local farmers, agribusinesses, and cooperatives who need those skills on a task or seasonal basis.

How it works
●	Skill-based profiles: Rural workers create profiles listing their skills, tools they own, experience level, and availability. Profile creation is guided, visual, and can be completed in under five minutes.
●	Proximity-first matching: SkillSetu uses location data to surface jobs 'Near You' — sorted by distance. A tractor mechanic sees openings within 5 km, 10 km, and 15 km, avoiding the need for expensive long-distance travel.
●	Direct application via call: Recognising that internet voice calls are more comfortable than text for many rural workers, SkillSetu features an 'Apply via Call' button that directly dials the job poster — no typing, no form-filling.
●	Daily rate transparency: Every job listing shows the offered daily rate (e.g., ₹500/day for tractor servicing, ₹450/day for wheat harvest crew). Workers know what they'll earn before applying.
●	Job categories: The board covers — Agricultural Equipment Mechanics, Harvesting Crew, Irrigation Technicians, Cold Storage Operators, Pesticide/Spray Technicians, Warehouse & Logistics Support.

The problem it solves
SkillSetu solves a market coordination failure: skilled rural workers and the agricultural employers who need them exist in the same geography but have no efficient mechanism to find each other. The result is underemployment for workers and unmet labour demand for employers. SkillSetu bridges this gap — keeping skilled talent in rural communities rather than pushing it toward cities.

